The paper deals with the Rendezvous problem for autonomous mobile robots, which is a classic problem in the field of multi-agent systems and robotics. The use of external-lights and L-algorithms is a common approach to solving this problem, which falls under the category of distributed algorithms. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the use of persistent memory and asynchronous settings, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the optimality of the algorithms in terms of the number of colors used, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
